kfasts and Suppers, at\nHolt's.\n\nL\u00bbl\na\nTr-i\n'S\nHOLT'S\nHOLT'S\n5 East 4th Street\nOpen All Night. Ladies' Room, 2d Floor\nW. T. Travers has Just completed an\nextended trip to New York.\nHeadquarters for Ladies' and Misses'\nWearables at Fine's Low Price Lead\ners, 201 Market, 7 E. Third 8t*\nWilmington Furniture Co.\nSome people, either Ifom difllflence or\nthe fear ot giving trouble, hesitate about\ngoing into a stor; unless they intend to buy.\nWe will give all such a cordial welcome\u2014\nit's a pleasure to us to be able to show these\nbeautiful spring goods.\n\nT\nwlj\nThere is an object lesson in one of our windows today\nwhich is illustrative of our entire stock. The window\ncontains a few summer curtains and the price tickets on\nthem are $1-00, $150 and $2.00 a pair. They don't\nlook like $100, $1.50 and $2.00 curtains and they are\nnot the kind you get in other stores at those prices. We\ninvite the person who contemplates purchasing any\nhouse furnishings this spring to examine our stock and\nmake comparisons.\nMattings, by the roll,\nRefrigerators\nPorch Rockers\nAwnings Let us estimate\n$6 to $40\n$11 to $60\n$1.75 to $6\nNinth and King Streets\nSEE WASHINGTON\nTHE HEART OF THE NATION\nTHREE-DAY TOUR\nI\nVIA\nPENNSYLVANIA RAILROAD\nTHURSDAY, May 7. 1908\nROUND-TRIP RATE $8.25 OR $10.75\nFROM WILMINGTON\nAccording to hotel selected.\nCovers necessary expense* for three days. Tickets good returning Tor tei\ndays.\nALL THE PRINCIPAL POINTS OF INTEREST IN THE NATIONAL CAPITAL\nDetailed Itineraries and full Information of Ticket Agents, or\nGEO, W. BOYD,\nGeneral Passenger Agent, Philadelphia, Pa.\nJ. R. WOOD,\nPassenger Traffic Manager.\nAuction Sale\nGoods Offered (or Sale Must Be Sold Regardless\nof Cost\nSale Starts Afternoon at 2.30 o'clock. Evening 7.30\nand continues daily until these goods are sold. Furni\nture, carpets, stoves, draperies and ladies' and gents'\nclothing. Going at a sacrifice.\nYOUR GAIN\nOUR LOSS\nW. S. Hoffman Co.\nN. W. Cor. Third and Shipley Streets.\nFINANCIAL.\nFINANCIAL\nAN\nINTESTATE ESTATE\nThat it, th\u00ab Est\u00e2t\u00ab of a person\nwho ha* died without leaving a\nWill, must be settled by an Ad\nministrator appointed by tha\nRegister of Wills. Thie company\nIs authorized by law to act in\nsuoh cases. The thorough know\nledge its officers have of the es\ntablished practice In making aet\ntlsments, its large capital and\nsurplus, and the very reasonable\nallowances made for its servioee\nare special inducements for the\nselection of\nSecurity Trust&\nSate Deposit Co.\n519 MARKET ST., WILMINGTON, DEL\nAnswering Questions\nWe are never too busy to answer\nthe questions of our patrons. The\nbanking knowledge of our officers\nand clerks is always at your com\nmand.\nWILMINGTON TRUST\nCOMPANY.\nTenth and Market Streets.\nT. C. duPont, Pr\u00e9sidant.\nHenry P. Scott, Vice-President\nPierre 8. duPont. Vice-President\nB. D. Townsend, Vloe-Proaldent\nWm. Winder Laird. Treasurer.\nDIRECTORS.\nT. C. duPont Baun Uancro.t Jr\nHenry P. Scott Cbarl*\u00ab C. Kurts.\nPierre 8. duPont John Biggs\nWilliam miles A. W. Soruanee\nHarlan O Scott Andrew C. a\n8. D. Townsend\n-'EQUITABLE\n'GUARANTEE ,Nn\nTRUST CO.\nN. W. Cor. Ninth and Market Sts.\nWilmington, Del\nLetters ot Credit\nand\nTraveUer's Cheques\non which money can be secured In any\npart of the world are kept on band and\nIssued by this Company at a moment's\nnotice, thus making It unnecessary to\ngo to Philadelphia for this purpose.\nThese provide the safest and moat\nconvenient way for traveler\u00ab either In\nthis country or abroad to carry fund\u00ab.\nWe shall be pleaaed to explain the de\ntails to any one Interested.\nEnglish currency kept constantly o\u00ab\nhand.\nDIRECTORS.\nJ. Wilkins Coech\nDr. J. A. Draper\nE. Brlnghurst. Jr. Willard Saulsbury\nJ. Smith Brennan\nJob. L. Carpenter\nOtho Nowland\nJohn Bancroft\nFranklin Taylor,\nRobert B. Wheels*\nJohn H. Danby.\nTbo*. H. Relish\nVictor B, Woolley\nHenry R. Thompson\nHa